## How to Test the Complete Flow 

### Step 1: Invite a Supplier (As the Vendor)
1. Ensure your Vite server is running (`npm run dev`).
2. Log in as your vendor account (`vendor@sarisari.ph`).
3. Navigate to **http://localhost:8000/seller/suppliers** in your browser.
4. Type in an email (e.g., `distributor@example.com`) and click **Send Invitation**.
5. You will see the Pending Invitation appear below. Click the **"Simulation Link"** on that invitation!

### Step 2: Register the Supplier (As the Supplier)
1. The Simulation Link will take you to the new Supplier Registration screen.
2. Fill out the details (Company Name: "Mega Supply Co.", Name: "Distributor", Password: "password").
3. Click **Create Supplier Account**. You can now log into this new account!

### Step 3: Create a Purchase Order (As the Vendor)
1. Go back to your vendor account (`vendor@sarisari.ph`).
2. Navigate to **http://localhost:8000/seller/purchase-orders**.
3. Click **Create New PO**.
4. Select "Mega Supply Co." as the supplier, fill out an address, and add some line items (select the products you made in Module 2). 
5. Click **Send to Supplier**!

### Step 4: Approve the PO (As the Supplier)
1. Log in as the new supplier account (`distributor@example.com`).
2. You will be greeted by the stunning **Supplier Dashboard**.
3. Click on the PO under "Recent Purchase Orders".
4. You will see the full PO review screen. Click **Approve & Prepare Goods**.
5. The PO status changes to `APPROVED` and the audit trail logs the change!

Try it out! Let me know if everything works perfectly and when you are ready to tackle **Module 4: Inventory Management**!
